[{"location":"#Sane-microscopy-image-labeling-in-Julia-1","page":"Sane microscopy image labeling in Julia","title":"Sane microscopy image labeling in Julia","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#","page":"Sane microscopy image labeling in Julia","title":"Sane microscopy image labeling in Julia","text":"This is collection of simple labeling functions specifically suited for quickly embedding labels in microscopy images. I'm hoping to cover common use-cases like adding timestamps, scalebars, transitions, and extra image details.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Sane microscopy image labeling in Julia","title":"Sane microscopy image labeling in Julia","text":"CurrentModule=MicroscopyLabels","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Sane microscopy image labeling in Julia","title":"Sane microscopy image labeling in Julia","text":"Modules = [MicroscopyLabels]\nOrder   = [:function, :type]","category":"page"},{"location":"#MicroscopyLabels.timestamp!-Tuple{ImageMetadata.ImageMeta}","page":"Sane microscopy image labeling in Julia","title":"MicroscopyLabels.timestamp!","text":"timestamp!(img; units)\n\nWrites the timestamp in the upper left corner of a multidimensional image img with the units units. Images are required to have at least the x, y, and time axes labeled, i.e. img should be or contain an AxisArray object with xyt axes. If additional axes are present, the timestamp will be written to all of them.\n\nExample\n\nusing AxisArrays\nusing MicroscopyLabels\n\ntmp = AxisArray(zeros(200, 200, 5), Axis{:x}(1:200), Axis{:y}(1:200), Axis{:time}(1:5))\ntimestamp!(tmp)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"}]
